	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101516920538793><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=4361&mid=101516920538793>To save time</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=4361&mid=101516920538793#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=64677><span id=Sage>xaanru</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>1101 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Mar 3rd 10:27 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.70]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I had about 16 of the patches, and decided to make the cloak just for fun. got tired of killing greens after about 20 minutes. Went to Surefall Galde. Several merchants had them in inventory for 1sp 4cp per patch. Scooped up 48 of them for a couple gold. Started combining. Had to buy 4 more, as I had 1 failure, and this is with 88 skill. Now I've got the cloak, which I have no use for, and I can trade it for the dagger, which I also have no use for. Guess I'll just give it away.<br><br>My point is, if you want/need one of these, go buy the patches in surefall, and you'l have the cloak in 10 minutes, for less than 1pp.<br><br>I would encourage you to kill spiderlings and spiders for silk, and combine, to get skill up. Never fail on silk combines and skill up to 21 is pretty quick.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
